TITLE: Chaining Selectors in TestCafe
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to chain selectors in TestCafe to locate DOM elements based on hierarchy and filtering. It finds all `ul` elements, then the `label` elements within them, and then the parent `div` with the class `someClass` for each label.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_183

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Selector('ul').find('label').parent('div.someClass')
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using TestCafe Snapshot API Shorthands for Properties (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the concise syntax using TestCafe's snapshot API shorthands to directly access DOM element properties (like `nodeType`) from a selector promise (e.g., `await selector.nodeType`). This works for both simple selectors and selectors with parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_197

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const nodeType = await selector.nodeType;

// or

const nodeType = await selector('someParam').nodeType;
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing Authentication User Roles in TestCafe
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create user roles for different account types in TestCafe. This helper file defines three roles: a regular user, a Facebook user, and an admin user, each with their own login sequences.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_158

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Role } from 'testcafe';

export var regularAccUser = Role('http://example.com/login', async t => {
    await t
        .typeText('#login', 'TestUser')
        .typeText('#password', 'testpass')
        .click('#sign-in');
});

export var facebookAccUser = Role('http://example.com/login', async t => {
    await t
        .click('#sign-in-with-facebook')
        .typeText('#email', 'testuser@mycompany.com')
        .typeText('#pass', 'testpass')
        .click('#submit');
});

export var admin = Role('http://example.com/login', async t => {
    await t
        .typeText('#login', 'Admin')
        .typeText('#password', 'adminpass')
        .click('#sign-in');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Enabling Test Concurrency
DESCRIPTION: These shell and javascript snippets show how to enable concurrent test execution in TestCafe. The command-line example uses the '-c' flag to specify the number of concurrent instances. The API example utilizes the '.concurrency()' method, configuring the runner to use multiple instances of each browser.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_140

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
testcafe -c 3 chrome tests/test.js
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using test controller outside test code with Page Model pattern in TestCafe
DESCRIPTION: Provides an example of how to access the test controller 't' within a page model class. This allows implementing reusable page actions, such as login, without explicitly passing 't' as a parameter by importing it directly into the page model module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_169

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { Selector, t } from 'testcafe';

export default class Page {
    constructor () {
        this.loginInput    = Selector('#login');
        this.passwordInput = Selector('#password');
        this.signInButton  = Selector('#sign-in-button');
    }
    async login () {
        await t
            .typeText(this.loginInput, 'MyLogin')
            .typeText(this.passwordInput, 'Pa$$word')
            .click(this.signInButton);
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing Fixture Hooks in TestCafe
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define fixture hooks that execute before and after all tests in a fixture. These hooks are useful for server-side setup and teardown operations that affect all tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_165

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
fixture `My fixture`
    .page `http://example.com`
    .before( async ctx => {
        /* fixture initialization code */
    })
    .after( async ctx => {
        /* fixture finalization code */
    });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using TestCafe Shorthand Methods for Dictionary Properties (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows the use of dedicated shorthand methods (`getStyleProperty`, `getAttribute`, `getBoundingClientRectProperty`) for cleaner access to values within dictionary-like snapshot properties (style, attributes, boundingClientRect).
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_199

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const width = await selector.getStyleProperty('width');
const id    = await selector.getAttribute('id');
const left  = await selector.getBoundingClientRectProperty('left');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using Initialization and Finalization Hooks in TestCafe Tests (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of test.before and test.after hooks to execute setup and teardown code in TestCafe tests. The before method runs code before the test, and after runs code after test completion. Dependencies: testcafe module. Hooks receive the test controller (t) for side effect operations, such as resource management or test context configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_176

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
test
    .before( async t => {
        /* test initialization code */
    })
    ('My Test', async t => {
        /* test code */
    })
    .after( async t => {
        /* test finalization code */
    });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Debugging TestCafe Tests on the Client Side
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the t.debug() method to pause test execution and inspect the page state using browser developer tools. The debugging interface allows step-by-step execution of test actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_161

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
fixture `My fixture`
    .page `https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example`;

test('My test', async t => {
    await t
        .debug()
        .setNativeDialogHandler(() => true)
        .click('#populate')
        .click('#submit-button');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Enabling Full-Page Screenshots via TestCafe Runner API (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates configuring the TestCafe test runner programmatically to take full-page screenshots by default. This is achieved by passing an options object with `fullPage: true` to the `runner.screenshots` method. Requires TestCafe v1.6.0 or later.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_55

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
runner.screenshots({
    fullPage: true
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Enabling Full-Page Screenshots via TestCafe CLI (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates enabling the full-page screenshot feature globally for a test run using the TestCafe command-line interface. The `-s` (or `--screenshots`) flag is used with the `fullPage=true` option to ensure all screenshots capture the entire page content. Requires TestCafe v1.6.0 or later.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_54

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
testcafe chrome test.js -s fullPage=true
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Opening a child window using t.openWindow
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to open a child window using the t.openWindow method in TestCafe. It imports Selector and ClientFunction from 'testcafe', defines a fixture and a test, opens a new window using t.openWindow, and then verifies the URL of the new window using t.eval and t.expect. This example illustrates how to interact with and validate content within a newly opened window.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { Selector, ClientFunction } from 'testcafe';

fixture `Test page`
    .page('https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example/');

test('Open a new window', async t => {
    await t.openWindow('http://example.com');

    const url = await t.eval(() => document.documentURI);

    await t.expect(url).eql('http://example.com');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Setting TypeScript Config Path via Runner API
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to set the TypeScript configuration path using the `runner.tsConfigPath` method in the TestCafe API.  This method takes the path to the TypeScript configuration file as an argument, and the runner will use this config file for TypeScript compilation during the test run. The config file path is "path/to/config.json".
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
runner.tsConfigPath('path/to/config.json');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Switching between windows using t.switchToWindow
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to switch between open windows using the t.switchToWindow method in TestCafe. It defines a fixture and a test, opens two pop-up windows, switches to the initial window and then to a specific window based on its URL host, and verifies the URL of each window using t.eval and t.expect. This example showcases how to manage and interact with multiple windows during a test.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_47

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture `Example page`
    .page('https://example.com');

test('Switch to a specific window', async t => {
    const initialWindow = await t.getCurrentWindow();
    const popUp1        = await t.openWindow('https://devexpress.com');
    const popUp2        = await t.openWindow('https://github.com');

    await t.switchToWindow(initialWindow);

    const url = t.eval(() => document.documentURI);

    await t.expect(url).eql('https://example.com/');

    await t
        .switchToWindow(w => w.url.host === 'github.com')
        .expect(url).eql('https://github.com');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Sharing variables between fixture hooks and test code in TestCafe
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to share values and objects between fixture hooks (before and after) and test functions using the fixture context object 'ctx' and accessing it in test code via 't.fixtureCtx'. Includes assigning to 'ctx' in hooks and reading/modifying it within tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_166

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture `Fixture1`
    .before(async ctx  => {
        ctx.someProp = 123;
    })
    .after(async ctx  => {
        console.log(ctx.newProp); // > abc
    });

test('Test1', async t => {
    console.log(t.fixtureCtx.someProp); // > 123
});

test('Test2', async t => {
    t.fixtureCtx.newProp = 'abc';
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Specifying Metadata for TestCafe Tests (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to attach metadata to a TestCafe test using the chainable `.meta()` method before defining the test details. Metadata can be specified using single key-value calls or an object, allowing for custom data points in test reports.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_115

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
test
    .meta('testID', 't-0005')
    .meta({ severity: 'critical', testedAPIVersion: '1.0' })
    ('MyTest', async t => { /* ... */});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Stopping TestCafe Run on First Fail via API (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to enable the 'stop on first fail' behavior programmatically using the TestCafe Runner API. The `stopOnFirstFail` option is set to `true` in the configuration object passed to the `runner.run()` method. This causes the test execution to terminate as soon as any test fails. Available since TestCafe v0.23.0.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_103

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
runner.run({ stopOnFirstFail: true })
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Filtering TestCafe Tests/Fixtures via API Metadata (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates filtering tests programmatically using the TestCafe Runner API's `filter` method. The provided callback function receives test and fixture metadata (`testMeta`, `fixtureMeta`) and returns `true` only for tests where `testMeta.mobile` is 'true' and `fixtureMeta.env` is 'staging'. This allows for complex conditional logic. Introduced in TestCafe v0.23.1.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_99

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
runner.filter((testName, fixtureName, fixturePath, testMeta, fixtureMeta) => {
    return testMeta.mobile === 'true' &&
        fixtureMeta.env === 'staging';
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Performing API Request and Assertion in TestCafe (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using the TestCafe `t.request` action to send an HTTP GET request to a specified URL and retrieve the response body. It then uses `t.expect` to assert that the response body contains the expected string 'Hello World'. This showcases the API testing capabilities introduced in TestCafe v1.20.0.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const responseBody = await t.request(`http://localhost:3000/helloworld`).body;

t.expect(responseBody).contains('Hello World') // true
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Taking Screenshot of a Specific Element (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Provides an example of using the `t.takeElementScreenshot` action to capture a screenshot of a particular page element identified by a Selector. The action takes the target element selector and the desired file path for the screenshot as arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_117

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { Selector } from 'testcafe';

fixture `My fixture`
    .page `http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example/`;

test('Take a screenshot of a fieldset', async t => {
    await t
        .click('#reusing-js-code')
        .click('#continuous-integration-embedding')
        .takeElementScreenshot(Selector('fieldset').nth(1), 'my-fixture/important-features.png');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Closing windows using t.closeWindow
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to close windows using the t.closeWindow method in TestCafe. It defines two tests: one that closes the current window and another that closes a specific window. It opens a new window using t.openWindow, closes it using t.closeWindow (either without arguments or with a window descriptor), and then verifies the URL of the remaining window using t.eval and t.expect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_48

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture `Example page`
    .page('http://www.example.com');

test('Close the current window', async t => {
    const window1 = await t.openWindow('http://devexpress.com');

    await t.closeWindow();

    const url = await t.eval(() => document.documentURI);

    await t.expect(url).eql('http://www.example.com/');
});

test('Close a specific window', async t => {
    const window1 = await t.openWindow('http://devexpress.com');

    await t.closeWindow(window1);
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Running TestCafe with Internet Proxy via API in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Explains how to programmatically set a proxy (with optional authentication) for TestCafe runs using runner.useProxy. Assumes usage in a TestCafe runner script. Input includes proxy credentials and address string. Output is all network traffic routed via the proxy during test execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_152

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
runner.useProxy('username:password@proxy.mycorp.com');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Automating user actions in multiple windows
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how TestCafe can automate user actions in multiple windows. It imports the Selector from 'testcafe', defines a fixture and a test, and uses the click and typeText methods to interact with elements within a pop-up window. It shows how TestCafe automatically switches to a newly opened window to continue test actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_45

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { Selector } from 'testcafe';

fixture `Login page`
    .page('https://login.wrike.com/login/');

const googleButton = Selector('div.login-panel-footer__login-with > button');

test('Login via Google', async t => {
    await t
        .click(googleButton)
        .typeText('input[type=email]', 'This text will be entered inside the pop-up');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling Page Caching Globally with Runner API - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Applies the 'disablePageCaching' option at the root of the runner.run method's options object, preventing cache usage during the entire test session. Requires an instantiated runner from TestCafe's API. Useful for test environments sensitive to authentication issues triggered by cache behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_69

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
runner.run({ disablePageCaching: true });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling Page Caching Via Configuration File - JSON
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the 'disablePageCaching' property in the TestCafe configuration JSON for global effect. Should be placed at the root level in the configuration file. Requires TestCafe version supporting this property. All tests will execute with caching disabled, mitigating login/session problems.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_70

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "disablePageCaching": true
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling TestCafe Syntax Validation via API (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to disable TestCafe's test syntax validation programmatically using the Runner API. The `disableTestSyntaxValidation` option is set to `true` within the `runner.run()` method's configuration object. This permits running dynamically generated or imported tests without explicit `fixture` or `test` calls in the source file. Introduced in TestCafe v0.23.1.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_101

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
runner.run({ disableTestSyntaxValidation: true })
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Accessing Shadow DOM Elements with Selector API
DESCRIPTION: This TestCafe test case demonstrates how to access and interact with elements within a Shadow DOM using the `selector.shadowRoot()` method. It first locates a shadow host element, then accesses its shadow root, and finally selects a paragraph within the shadow tree to assert its text content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_44

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Selector } from 'testcafe'

fixture `Target Shadow DOM elements`
    .page('https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example')

test('Get text within shadow tree', async t => {
    const shadowRoot = Selector('div').withAttribute('id', 'shadow-host').shadowRoot();
    const paragraph  = shadowRoot.child('p');

    await t.expect(paragraph.textContent).eql('This paragraph is in the shadow tree');
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling TestCafe Syntax Validation via CLI (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates running TestCafe tests in Safari while disabling the default syntax validation using the `--disable-test-syntax-validation` flag. This allows running tests from files that don't explicitly contain `fixture` or `test` directives, useful for dynamically loaded or generated tests. Available since TestCafe v0.23.1.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_100

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
testcafe safari test.js --disable-test-syntax-validation
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Overriding Fixture Default Page on a Per-Test Basis in TestCafe (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to override the default fixture's page URL for individual tests by chaining .page to the test declaration in TestCafe. The first test uses the fixture's page, while the second starts at a custom page. Dependencies: testcafe module. Parameters include the URL string for the page method. Only works for compatible TestCafe versions supporting per-test page assignment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_175

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture `MyFixture`
    .page `http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example`;

test('Test1', async t => {
    // Starts at http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example
});

test
    .page `http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/blog/`
    ('Test2', async t => {
        // Starts at http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/blog/
    });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling Screenshots using Runner API - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Utilizes the JavaScript TestCafe runnerâ€™s run method with the 'disableScreenshots' option set to true to turn off screenshot functionality for the entire test run. Requires a valid runner object. No screenshots are taken regardless of t.takeScreenshot calls or test failures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_64

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
runner.run({ disableScreenshots: true });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Sharing Variables Between Hooks and Test Code with t.ctx in TestCafe (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to share state between fixture hooks, test hooks, and test code by using the t.ctx property in TestCafe. The example sets a property in a beforeEach hook, accesses it in the test, and confirms its persistence in the after hook. Dependencies: testcafe module. The shared context allows for flexible inter-test variable management without polluting global scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_177

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture `Fixture1`
    .beforeEach(async t  => {
        t.ctx.someProp = 123;
    });

test
    ('Test1', async t => {
        console.log(t.ctx.someProp); // > 123
    })
    .after(async t => {
        console.log(t.ctx.someProp); // > 123
    });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Filtering Selector's Matched Set by Attribute in TestCafe JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Presents the withAttribute method to filter DOM elements possessing a specific attribute with a given value, then selects the nth matching instance. Requires the 'testcafe' Selector API. Inputs are attribute name and value; output is a Selector for the targeted element, constrained by attribute filtering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_155

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const el = Selector('div').withAttribute('attributeName', 'value').nth(2);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Taking a Screenshot in TestCafe Test - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a basic TestCafe fixture and test which navigates to a specified URL and captures a screenshot using t.takeScreenshot(). No screenshot path needs to be set in the runner or config file - defaults will be used if unspecified. Dependencies include TestCafe installed in the environment. The test expects no input and outputs a screenshot image.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_61

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
fixture `My fixture`
    .page `https://example.com`;

test('Take a screenshot', async t => {
    await t.takeScreenshot();
});
```

