TITLE: Skipping and Running Specific Tests and Fixtures in TestCafe (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: These examples illustrate the use of fixture.skip, test.skip, fixture.only, and test.only to control which tests and fixtures run. All tests in a skipped fixture are omitted, while the only method ensures only designated tests run. Dependencies: testcafe module. This approach is useful for focusing on or ignoring tests during suites, and is limited to compatible TestCafe versions supporting these APIs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_174

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture.skip `Fixture1`; // All tests in this fixture will be skipped

test('Fixture1Test1', () => {});
test('Fixture1Test2', () => {});

fixture `Fixture2`;

test('Fixture2Test1', () => {});
test.skip('Fixture2Test2', () => {}); // This test will be skipped
test('Fixture2Test3', () => {});
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fixture.only `Fixture1`;
test('Fixture1Test1', () => {});
test('Fixture1Test2', () => {});

fixture `Fixture2`;
test('Fixture2Test1', () => {});
test.only('Fixture2Test2', () => {});
test('Fixture2Test3', () => {});

// Only tests in Fixture1 and the Fixture2Test2 test will run
```

