TITLE: Accessing Warnings in Custom TestCafe Reporter (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to access warnings generated during a test run within the `reportTestDone` method of a custom TestCafe reporter. The `testRunInfo` object passed to the method now contains a `warnings` array, which can be iterated over to report or log these warnings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/devexpress/testcafe/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_94

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async reportTestDone (name, testRunInfo, meta) {
    const warnings    = testRunInfo.warnings;
    const hasWarnings = !!warnings.length;

    if(hasWarnings) {
        this.newline()
            .write('Warnings:');

        warnings.forEach(warning => {
            this.newline()
                .write(warning);
        });
    }
}
```

